As governed by the Energy Gap Law, the non-radiative voltage losses could be increased with decreasing charge-transfer-state energies. Therefore, the development of high-performance ultra-narrow bandgap OSC is often hindered by strong non-radiative process and suffers low Voc in constructing TOSCs29. Surprisingly, despite BTPSeV-4F shows narrower Egopt, the Voc of BTPSV-4F and BTPSeV-4F based OSCs are quite similar. To investigate the reasons behind the unusual phenomenon of the Voc, we studied the energy losses in both devices. The total voltage loss can be calculated by the following equation:492Eloss=Eg−qVoc=(Eg−qVocSQ)+(qVOCSQ−qVOCrad)+(qVOCrad−qVOC)=ΔE1+ΔE2+ΔE3,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
