				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${E}_{{{{{\rm{loss}}}}}}=	 {E}_{g}-q{V}_{{{{{\rm{oc}}}}}}\\ \,=	 ({E}_{g}-q{V}_{oc}^{SQ})+(q{V}_{OC}^{SQ}-q{V}_{OC}^{{{{{\rm{rad}}}}}})+(q{V}_{OC}^{{{{{\rm{rad}}}}}}-q{V}_{OC})\\ \,=	 \varDelta {E}_{1}+\varDelta {E}_{2}+\varDelta {E}_{3},$$\end{document}where Eg is the optical bandgap of the corresponding active layers, q is the elementary charge, ΔE1 is the radiative loss above bandgap, ΔE2 is the radiative loss below bandgap, and ΔE3 is the nonradiative loss. The ΔE3 is equal to qΔVnr, and ΔVnr is the non-radiative recombination voltage loss, which can be calculated from the EQEEL of the devices by the equation of3ΔVnr=kTqln1EQEEL\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
